{"tid":153424,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"民族黨: 支持香港獨立 維持現況與自殺無異","createTime":"2017-03-12T14:34:13.000Z","updateTime":"2018-09-22T07:14:49.000Z","uid":70063,"like":71,"dislike":3,"uniUserReply":0,"replies":[{"pid":"73ecfd4aa5056132bfded36451e0eb98a950154c","tid":153424,"uid":70063,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-03-12T14:34:13.000Z","msg":"民族黨發言人周浩輝：本黨主張香港獨立，任由香港「維持現況」與自殺無異。<br />\n(&ldquo;My party supports independence. Maintaining the status quo would mean suicide,&rdquo;)<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/hknationalparty/posts/619499834915641\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fhknationalparty%2Fposts%2F619499834915641&d=xz9%2BKahtnlDLfwjNDOwuFJZgE6vMW1KEzMhkvokIvkY%3D&h=6418a93c\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.facebook.com/hknationalparty/posts/619499834915641</a><br />\n<br />\nHong Kong National Party speaker causes outrage in seminar comparing city&rsquo;s issues to Tibetan experience<br />\n<br />\nJason Chow Ho-fai says both places have been deprived of self-determination<br />\n<br />\nA leading figure of a radical localist party has likened the influence of mainland China on Hong Kong to Tibet&rsquo;s experience after the Communist Party established control of the region in the early 1950s.<br />\n<br />\nJason Chow Ho-fai, spokesman from the pro-independence Hong Kong National Party, presented at a seminar titled &ldquo;New Tibet &ndash; Hong Kong under re-colonisation&rdquo;.<br />\n<br />\nBut a total of 15 people walked out in protest at different times throughout the session. The event was held by City University&rsquo;s students&rsquo; union to mark the 58th anniversary of the Tibetan uprising.<br />\n<br />\nThose who left held slogans or banners with the words &ldquo;Opposition to Tibetan independence&rdquo; or &ldquo;Anti-Tibetan independence, Anti-Separatism&rdquo;.<br />\n<br />\nChow said that the political situation faced by Hong Kong was similar to that of Tibet.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Both places have been deprived of the rights of national self-determination &hellip; how do we want to go forward into the future?&rdquo; Chow asked.<br />\n<br />\nHe claimed that evidence of &ldquo;re-colonisation&rdquo; of the city by the mainland included schoolchildren speaking Putonghua in private conversations, and some companies listing competency in the language as a job requirement.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;My party supports independence. Maintaining the status quo would mean suicide,&rdquo; he said.<br />\n<br />\nHe urged Hong Kong to start preparing for independence, such as reducing reliance on the mainland.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Can we stop purchasing things from Chinese companies? Can we stop considering our local culture as inferior?&rdquo; he said.<br />\n<br />\nBut the audience questioned whether Hong Kong could be sustainable if it became independent.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;If we cannot purchase water from the mainland, what can we do? If we introduced an army from another country, are we going to be another country&rsquo;s colony?&rdquo; a woman asked.<br />\n<br />\nOthers also questioned how Hong Kong could establish strong diplomatic ties with other countries if it were independent.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/2077950/hong-kong-national-party-speaker-causes-outrage-seminar?utm_source&amp;utm_medium&amp;utm_campaign=SCMPSocialNewsfeed\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fnews%2Fhong-kong%2Fpolitics%2Farticle%2F2077950%2Fhong-kong-national-party-speaker-causes-outrage-seminar%3Futm_source%26utm_medium%26utm_campaign%3DSCMPSocialNewsfeed&d=xz9%2BKahtnlDLfwjNDOwuFJZgE6vMW1KEzMhkvokIvkY%3D&h=115f1edd\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.scmp.com/news/hong-kong/politics/article/2077950/hong-kong-national-party-speaker-causes-outrage-seminar?utm_source&amp;utm_medium&amp;utm_campaign=SCMPSocialNewsfeed</a>"},{"pid":"f96569e23dbdbca50b55eb6e203c15a19c2d10bf","tid":153424,"uid":53705,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-03-12T14:36:26.000Z","msg":"之前又話發起第二次香港保衛戰<br />\n<br />\n發起左未??"},{"pid":"50545fc6b21ef15f2db640578c63176d9e5ab50b","tid":153424,"uid":70063,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-03-12T14:39:10.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"color: red;\">'Doable' for Hong Kong to seek independence</span>: Bookseller Lam Wing-kee<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/doable-for-hong-kong-to/2885976.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.channelnewsasia.com%2Fnews%2Fasiapacific%2Fdoable-for-hong-kong-to%2F2885976.html&d=xz9%2BKahtnlDLfwjNDOwuFJZgE6vMW1KEzMhkvokIvkY%3D&h=704c6e80\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/asiapacific/doable-for-hong-kong-to/2885976.html</a><br />\n<br />\nChannel NewsAsia's WEI DU: Many young people in Hong Kong think the &quot;One Country, Two Systems&quot; won&rsquo;t work out. The best way forward is-<br />\n<br />\nLAM WING-KEE: <span style=\"color: red;\">Independence</span>. My personal opinion, and I am not afraid to say, is that it&rsquo;s <span style=\"color: red;\">doable</span>.<br />\n<br />\nIn a marriage, if the man treats the woman badly, the woman will leave. It&rsquo;s normal. She wants her happiness too. The Communist party wants to control everyone, but it&rsquo;s not elected, it has no legitimacy. It has no respect for human rights. So when people demand independence, they have a reason. It&rsquo;s the same for Hong Kong."},{"pid":"ad24893e583a1204176cba9ef68993668b23fb7d","tid":153424,"uid":57705,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-03-12T14:44:11.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"6160206397955e90c13e1feb64ac7fd7450d6215","tid":153424,"uid":70063,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2017-03-12T14:45:07.000Z","msg":"push"},{"pid":"15df4ae84d026678c74e56410d34dbfc2459709a","tid":153424,"uid":22858,"like":0,"